
[1]larboard

   L'ARBOARD, n. [Board, bord, is a side; but I know the meaning of lar.
   The Dutch use bakboard, and the Germans backbord.]

   The left hand side of a ship, when a person stands with his face to the
   head; opposed to starboard.

      L'ARBOARD, a. Pertaining to the left hand side of a ship; as the
                              larboard quarter.
